Class Compiler

  • java.lang.Object
    • Compiler
  • public class Compiler
extends java.lang.Object
    Class for the compiler. The compiler can compile from an AbstractSyntaxTree.

      • If

        private void If​(AbstractSyntaxTree AST,
                int index)
        Write an if (/else) condition in the LLVM IR language by computing the condition and using the result to make a conditionnal jump in the code to the right label. The compiler can also remove empty if (/else) conditions.
        Parameters:
        AST - the AbstractSyntaxTree whose label is If

      • For

        private void For​(AbstractSyntaxTree AST,
                 int index)
        Write a for loop in the LLVM IR language by assigning the counter variable to the initial value then comparing the counter variable to the maximal value. If the counter variable is less equal than the maximal value, we do the code of the for loop then increment the counter variable by the increment value. The compiler can also remove empty for loops.
        Parameters:
        AST - the AbstractSyntaxTree whose label is While

      • While

        private void While​(AbstractSyntaxTree AST,
                   int index)
        Write a while loop in the LLVM IR language by computing the condition and using the result to make a conditionnal jump in the code to the right label. The compiler can also remove empty while loops.
        Parameters:
        AST - the AbstractSyntaxTree whose label is While

      • operate

        private void operate​(AbstractSyntaxTree AST)
        Call the corresponding operation with the good operator. If the AST is a VarName, we load it.
        Parameters:
        AST - the AST corresponding to the operator
